  <thing id="spSGWayPt4" name="Waypoint" description="As {i}guiding star{/i} (Advanced Player’s Guide) but you may be attuned to a maximum of 1 location per caster level, and may transfer an attunement to another creature with a touch with an additional casting of this spell. A transferred attunement removes the attunement from you permanently, and only grants it to a new creature for 1 day/level.\n\n{i}Guiding Star{/i}:\nYou form a bond with your surroundings when you cast this spell. For the remaining duration of the spell you can always, as a standard action, determine your approximate distance from that area as well as the direction you must travel in order to reach it. You cannot determine the location of the area if you are on a different plane. The area counts as &quot;very familiar&quot; for the purposes of teleport or similar spells. You can only attune yourself to one location at a time. If you cast the spell at another spot you lose the ability to locate your original area." compset="Spell" summary="Know approximate distance from where you cast this spell.">
