  <thing id="spSGWryBrd" name="Weary Burden" description="As {i}slow{/i}, but effect is to increase target’s encumbrance by 1 step to a maximum of heavy encumbrance.\n\n{i}Slow{/i}:\nAn affected creature moves and attacks at a drastically slowed rate. Creatures affected by this spell are staggered and can take only a single move action or standard action each turn, but not both (nor may it take full-round actions). Additionally, it takes a -1 penalty on attack rolls, AC, and Reflex saves. A slowed creature moves at half its normal speed (round down to the next 5-foot increment), which affects the creature&apos;s jumping distance as normal for decreased speed. Multiple slow effects don&apos;t stack. Slow counters and dispels haste." compset="Spell" summary="One subject/level takes only one action/round, -1 to AC, Reflex saves, and attack rolls.">
